generalfeedback.text: Since we are given the turning point of the parabola is \(-4,-4\), and using completing the square we have that the equation must be of the form \[ y = a(x +4)^2 -3 \] Substituting the \(x\) and \(y\) values from the other point into this equation and rearranging gives \[ -19 = a(0 + 4)^2 -3 \implies -19 = 16a - 3 \implies a = -1 \] Hence the equation of the quadratic is \[ y = -(x +4)^2 -3 \]
